論文字彙與句型
週四
		          晚間6:30~9:15
6,300
一班30人，適合相當於全民英檢中高級程度者；學習論文型態的句型結構與字彙用法，並撰寫文獻回顧，描述研究成果。


 授課教師及詳細課程說明


《授課教師》Edward Partington

《課程說明》
This course is  intended for graduate students or those interested in  academic writing.
			                Students will  be doing a series of tasks involving the following:
			                Writing General-Specific Texts; Problem Process, and Solution; Data Commentary;
			                Writing Summaries; Writing Critiques; Constructing A Research Paper. More time
			                wiIl  be devoted to writing and understanding  Introductions, Methods Sections,
			                Results.
			                In addition to  preparing the tasks ahead of each class, students wil1 have  the option of
			                submi吐ing up to three pages of  their own academic work.
			                This course is recommended  for those students whose English is already at an
advancedlevel.
		                





 摘要與計畫寫作
週五
                    晚間6:30～9:15
6,300
一班30人，適合相當於全民英檢中高級程度者；學習如何精讀參考文獻，引述作者論點，撰寫摘要(abstract)，以利撰寫研究計畫。


 授課教師及詳細課程說明



《授課教師》Edward Partington
 
《課程說明》
			                This advanced academic writing course deals  with the above matters through a series
of very chal1enging  tasks. The first five weeks wiU be devoted to summarizing and
paraphrasing. The remaining five weeks  will be shared equally by Abstracts,
Literature Reviews and Introductions to academic papers. Students will  have a
significant load of homework to finish in addition to preparing the tasks each week.
In addition, students will have the option to submit  up to three pages of their own
academic work. It will be retumed  the following week with comments and
correctlOns.
This course  is also intended mainly for graduate students working on their theses or
dissertations.  Undergraduates intending to soon go to graduate school will also find it
of great interest.
			               


 



高級寫作
週二
                    晚間6:30~9:15
6,300

一班30人，適合相當於全民英檢中高級，欲加強寫作能力者；學習如何精確地表達主題，瞭解寫作風格的意義，以展現個人寫作特色。


 授課教師及詳細課程說明



《授課教師》Edward Partington

                            《課程說明》
This course is intended for upper-intermediate to advanced students interested in improving their writing. The course will cover the following areas:
                            1. Understanding the meaning of style and correctness in writing.
                            2. Actions.-when to use verbs and when to nominalize less.
                            3. Characters- Your choice of subject and related issues.
                            4. Cohesion and Coherence.
                            5. Emphasis.
                            6. Concision, Shape and Elegance.
                            Text: None. Teacher-Generated Materials.










 
 


 
C.《暑期班》：106年7月10日～9月15日，晚間6:30~9:15，共10週。


 
《考試課程》


 


班     
			        別
